text="Properties of isomorphism">Properties of <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00L0.xml"
addr="jms-00L0"
title="Isomorphic sets">isomorphism</fr:link></fr:title><fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>25</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>The concept of <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00L0.xml"
addr="jms-00L0"
title="Isomorphic sets">isomorphism</fr:link> between two sets satisfies laws like those of an <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00L4.xml"
addr="jms-00L4"
title="Equivalence relation">equivalence relation</fr:link>. In particular:</fr:p><fr:ol><fr:li>reflexivity: <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A\cong  A]]></fr:tex>;</fr:li>
 <fr:li>transitivity: <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A\cong  B \land  B \cong  C \implies  A \cong  C]]></fr:tex>;</fr:li>
 <fr:li>symmetry: <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A\cong  B \implies  B\cong  A]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li></fr:ol></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
